===Noun===
''National Incident Management System (NIMS)''
# A system designed and implemented by the Department of Homeland Security by request of President Bush.  It is designed to facilitate effective practices of emergency preparedness and response.  The goal is to enable responders at all levels to work effectively at incidents of all sizes.  The NIMS framework will be able to applied to incidents regadless of cause, size, or comlexity.